Diamond::

She saw the two bots that had shot at her and she shook her rattle.  
She knew that she should try to escape, but they wouldn't leave her 
alone.  She transformed into bot mode and pulled the cover off the 
drain.  She then drew her quazar pistol and glared at them. "OK guys, 
I'll give you a little credit. First you were nice enough to drag me 
from my burning ship. Thank you.  Then you offer to  fix me up. That 
was sweet. but now you want to kill me. I can't blame you.  After I 
killed the maximal leader Quantis at his home back on Cybertron, they 
wanted me dead too.  And I would have gotten away with it. but my 
predacon council leader decided to make a deal and turned me in. So, 
I guess I'm just a wanted bot."  she sighed a very bored sigh."Now 
gentle bots, if you will pardon me. I must take my leave. Unless you 
can think of one good reason for me to stay?"  She smiled.  She knew 
that if she could peak thier interest, she may have use for the one 
that saved her.  She really liked him.  Her fangs itched, which 
usually was her instincts telling her something. She transformed into 
rattle snake and curled up around the drain. "Well?"
